body:
Support question here - I am looking for a robust and performant way to update an input field's text programmatically, _where the input field has `defaultValue` instead of `value`_.

Something like this:

```js
render: function(){

  return (

      <input
        id="pickupField"
        tabIndex="1"
        placeholder=""
        className="order-form-input"
        onFocus={this.disableAddresses}
        onBlur={() => {
            this.enableAddresses();
            this.fieldChange('address');
        }}
        // we use defaultValue, not value
        defaultValue={(order.pickup || {}).address || ''}  
        ref="pickupAddress"
        hintText={(this.state.hideHintText) ? "" : "Enter the pickup address"}
        floatingLabelFixed={true}
        floatingLabelText="Pickup Address"
      />
   )
}

```

The problem I am having is that I want to sync with the database, upon the "onBlur" event of the input field. If I use `value` instead of `defaultValue`, _I can get this to work_, but there are two problems I see with using value instead of defaultvalue:

(a) much less performant => updating the react component state on every keystroke
(b) more importantly, it makes my database sync logic more complex, because I will update the React component state on every keystroke, but only sync with the database on every onBlur. I'd rather not have to write that logic, if possible.

I asked this question on SO:

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41133182/react-uncontrolled-component-updating-the-input-fields-despite-presence-of-def

Please let me know if you have any ideas, thanks!
